annotationA: Phosphotidylinositol 3 kinase 59F, also known as Vacuolar protein sorting 34, is a lipid kinase that is required for formation of Phosphatidylinositol 3-phosphate. It functions in a core protein complex that includes Atg6 and Vps15 and is involved in the control of vesicle trafficking, including autophagy, endocytosis and phagocytosis; Belongs to the PI3/PI4-kinase family
annotationB: Autophagy-related 14; It is involved in the biological process described with: regulation of autophagy; autophagy; positive regulation of autophagy
